IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE FAMILY PRACTICE TRAINING AND RELEVANT HEALTHCARE EDUCATION AND SERVICES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE FAMILY PRACTICE TRAINING AND, IN SUPPORT OF THAT END, RELEVANT HEALTHCARE EDUCATION AND SERVICES.
IRS990.Desc: THE LINCOLN FAMILY MEDICINE PROGRAM (LFMP) IS ONE OF THE COUNTRY'S PREEMINENT COMMUNITY-BASED RESIDENCY PROGRAMS, ATTRACTING SOME OF THE BRIGHTEST RESIDENT PHYSICIANS IN THE U.S. AND AROUND THE WORLD. A FULLY ACCREDITED PROGRAM, LFMP IS AFFILIATED WITH THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA MEDICAL CENTER. THE LINCOLN FAMILY MEDICINE PROGRAM PLAYS A CRUCIAL ROLE IN MEETING THE MIDWEST'S NEED FOR PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIANS AND OPERATES THE LINCOLN FAMILY MEDICINE CENTER (LFMC). THE LFMC IS THE PRIMARY EDUCATION SITE FOR THE TRAINING OF RESIDENTS OF LFMP. FUNCTIONING AS A MODEL GROUP PRACTICE, LFMP RESIDENTS CARE FOR PATIENTS IN THE CENTER BY APPOINTMENT.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: LINCOLN PEDIATRIC HOSPITALISTS WORK CLOSELY WITH VARIOUS SPECIALISTS, INCLUDING FAMILY MEDICINE PROVIDERS, GENERAL SURGEONS, AND OTHER PEDIATRICIANS TO PROVIDE COMPREHENSIVE CARE DURING A CHILD'S HOSPITALIZATION. THE PEDIATRIC HOSPITALISTS SEE PATIENTS IN VARIOUS DEPARTMENTS, INCLUDING PEDIATRIC ACUTE CARE, NEWBORN NURSERY, EMERGENCY DEPARTMENT, LABOR AND DELIVERY, NEONATAL INTENSIVE CARE AND PEDIATRIC INTENSIVE CARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: SCHOOL COMMUNITY INTERVENTION AND PREVENTION (SCIP) IS A PROGRAM DESIGNED TO BRING TOGETHER FAMILIES, SCHOOLS AND THE COMMUNITY TO SUPPORT STUDENT BEHAVIORIAL AND EMOTIONAL HEALTH. SCIP'S MISSION IS TO PROVIDE AN EFFECTIVE PREVENTION AND EARLY INTERVENTION PROCESS FOR YOUTH WITH BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CONCERNS, SO THEY MAY ACHIEVE HEALTHY, PRODUCTIVE LIVES. SCIP WORKS WITH SCHOOLS BY PROVIDING TOOLS AND RESOURCES TO ADDRESS BEHAVIORAL AND EMOTIONAL HEALTH ISSUES THAT IMPACT CHILDREN, ADOLESCENTS AND THEIR FAMILIES.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: OTHER PROGRAMS SUCH AS THE LINCOLN MEDICAL ACUPUNCTURE AND STEPPING STONES FOR FAMILIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INCOME FROM THE ENDOWMENT FUNDS IS USED TO SUPPORT THE RESIDENCY PROGRAM AS PER DONORS' INSTRUCTIONS.

THE PARTNERSHIP ACCOUNTS FOR UNCERTAINTIES IN ACCOUNTING FOR INCOME TAX ASSETS AND LIABILITIES USING GUIDANCE INCLUDED IN FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD (FASB) ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION (ASC) 740, INCOME TAXES. THE PARTNERSHIP RECOGNIZES THE EFFECT OF INCOME TAX POSITIONS ONLY IF THOSE POSITIONS ARE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT OF BEING SUSTAINED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE PROVIDED IN THE BYLAWS, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE MAY ACT ON BEHALF OF THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS BETWEEN SCHEDULED MEETINGS THEREOF IF A SPECIAL MEETING OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS CANNOT BE ARRANGED DUE TO A LACK OF QUORUM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BRYAN HEALTH AND CHI HEALTH ST. ELIZABETH SERVE AS MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE HOSPITALS APPOINT BOARD MEMBERS AS PER LMEP'S BYLAWS. SAINT ELIZABETH APPOINTS ONE PHYSICIAN BOARD MEMBER AND BRYAN HEALTH APPOINTS TWO PHYSICIAN BOARD MEMBERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR QUESTIONS AND COMMENTS AT A REGULAR BOARD MEETING PRIOR TO FILING FORM 990. THE CFO AND PRACTICE ADMINISTRATOR REVIEWS FORM 990 AND COMPARES IT TO THE AGENCY'S RECORDS. THE CFO AND PRACTICE ADMINISTRATOR APPROVES AND SIGNS THE FORM 990.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL DIRECTORS, OFFICERS, AND KEY EMPLOYEES ARE PROVIDED CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS ANNUALLY. THEY ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN AND DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS. ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS ARE NOTED. ACTIVITIES THAT MAY BE AFFECTED BY THAT POTENTIAL CONFLICT ARE MONITORED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESIDENT'S COMPENSATION WAS DETERMINED BY THE SELECTION COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. COMPENSATION WAS SET BASED ON COMPARABLE LOCAL SALARY DATA AND WAS ESTABLISHED AT THE TIME OF THE CONTRACTUAL AGREEMENT. THE COMPENSATION OF THE CFO AND PRACTICE ADMINISTRATOR IS SET BY THE PRESIDENT AND IS BASED ON COMPARABLE LOCAL SALARY DATA. THE SALARIES ARE REVIEWED ANNUALLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: LMEP DOES NOT MAKE ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC.

THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE OVERSIGHT OF THE AUDIT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND FOR THE SELECTION OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT. THIS PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
